      "content": "That makes sense, but i've been reading some stuff online saying that the whole idea of international law or the UN is kinda outdated and actually just makes things worse by giving too much power to certain countries. do historians see those views as legitimate criticisms of the system, or is that just seen as a fringe way of looking at it?",
